      • getFileSystemFolder

        public java.lang.String getFileSystemFolder()
        Returns the folder path of the repository. The default value is "repository" and can be changed with a properties file or with the method setFileSystemFolder(String). This property is only used when the repository type is "filesystem".
        Returns:
        the folder path of the repository.

      • setFileSystemFolder

        public void setFileSystemFolder(java.lang.String fileSystemFolder)
        Sets the folder path of the repository. This property is only used when the repository type is "filesystem".
        Parameters:
        fileSystemFolder - folder, in the filesystem, that the repository will use to save the files

      • getMongoDatabaseName

        public java.lang.String getMongoDatabaseName()
        Returns the database name used for the repository. The default value is "kurento-repository" and can be changed with a properties file or with the method setMongoDatabaseName(String). This property is only used when the repository type is "mongodb".
        Returns:
        the database name.

      • setMongoDatabaseName

        public void setMongoDatabaseName(java.lang.String mongoDatabaseName)

      • getMongoGridFSCollectionName

        public java.lang.String getMongoGridFSCollectionName()
        Returns the name of the gridfs collection used for the repository. The default value is "fs" and can be changed with a properties file or with the method setMongoGridFSCollectionName(String). This property is only used when the repository type is "mongodb".
        Returns:
        the name of the gridfs collection.

      • setMongoGridFSCollectionName

      • getMongoURLConnection

        public java.lang.String getMongoURLConnection()
        Returns the connection to mongo database. The default value is "mongodb://localhost" and can be changed with a properties file or with the method setMongoURLConnection(String). This property is only used when the repository type is "mongodb".
        Returns:
        the connection to mongo database.

      • setMongoURLConnection

        public void setMongoURLConnection(java.lang.String mongoURLConnection)

        Parameters:
        mongoURLConnection - connection URL for the mong database
